ce:section.ce:para:
Luminescent MOFs (LMOFs) have been widely developed as a chemical sensor for detecting various metal ions, anions, small organic molecules and biomolecules due to its advantages of large specific surface area, predictable nanostructures and adjustable pore sizes [52]. Here, Eu-MOFs was synthesized according to the synthesis methods and conditions described in the literature [51]. Based on the crystallographic information file (CIF) reported in the literature, it was simulated by diamond that Eu3+ in Eu-MOFs coordinates with eight coordination atoms, which include two nitrogen atoms from one phen ligand, five carboxylic acid oxygen atoms from atpt ligands and one terminal water molecule. Every two Eu3+ are bridged by carboxylic acid groups of atpt ligands, forming the basic unit of Eu-MOFs topological structure (
                        Fig. S1
                        ). These basic units are further connected by carboxylic acid groups of atpt ligands to form a porous framework, which provides the possibility for the enrichment of target metal ions (
                        Fig. S2
                        ). Fluorescent carbon dots (CDs) are a new type of carbon nanomaterials developed in recent years, which are favored by researchers for their unique advantages. Using nontoxic solvents and economical green materials to prepare CDs is a key issue that should be taken into consideration into green synthesis strategy [53]. Black wolfberry is rich in protein, polysaccharide, amino acids, vitamins, minerals, trace elements and other nutritional components, and becomes an ideal material for preparing CDs [38]. It is worth noting that the synthesis method of CDs@Eu-MOFs was the same as that of Eu-MOFs except CDs addition, and the synthesized CDs@Eu-MOFs inherited simultaneously the excellent optical properties of CDs and Eu3+. The ratiometric fluorescence sensor constructed by this method overcame the disadvantage that the single wavelength fluorescence sensor was easily affected by the factors such as concentration, environment and excitation intensity, and had a good application prospect.
